name: Carport Solar
notes:
Hey Michael,
 
Following our brief discussion about the carports, I wanted to share an idea—has anyone explored installing solar panels on them through an Energy Service Agreement (ESA)? If not, I’d be happy to look into the feasibility and model potential returns.
 
An ESA wouldn’t require any upfront capital investment. The provider covers the cost of equipment and installation, and in return, charges a rate that’s typically 10-40% lower than local electricity costs. This could be a creative way to reduce house meter expenses while also lowering electricity costs for vacant units, which often add up over time.
 
Would you be open to me researching this further? Also, do you have an estimate of how much the properties currently spend on house meter electricity and vacant unit utilities each month or annually? That information would help assess the potential savings.
 
Looking forward to your thoughts.
